[30;1m4421 | [0m[35m    In linear space, the sequence starts at ``base ** start``[0m

[30;1m4423 | [0m[35m    (see `endpoint` below).[0m
[30;1m4424 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m364 | [0m[35m    the output is a tensor of densities such that the densities at index *i* in the output[0m
[30;1m365 | [0m[35m    are given by the samples at index *i* in *sample* parameterized by the value of *alpha*[0m
[30;1m366 | [0m[35m    at index *i*.[0m
[30;1m367 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m83 | [0m[35m    """The base class of a module.[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m85 | [0m[35m    A module represents a computation component. One can think of module as a computation machine.[0m
[30;1m86 | [0m[35m    A module can execute forward and backward passes and update parameters in a model.[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35m    We aim to make the APIs easy to use, especially in the case when we need to use the imperative[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35m    API to work with multiple modules (e.g. stochastic depth network).[0m
[30;1m89 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m2272[0m[34m of [0m[33m2800[0m[31m ]--[0m
